            . Between nine and ten in the morning of the 20th of July, I saw the prisoner talking to a woman in Prescot Street; they soon parted; she went away and the prisoner walked by the prosecutor's house, and then he went in. I said to a man that was near me, stay a little,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177209090007"></xptr> and we shall see what the man is about. I soon perceived him in the parlour; I saw him take up the sugar dish and milk pot, and bring them towards the door; then he saw the other man and me standing in the passage, and returned them to the place again; the milk was spilt and the sugar was scattered about the table; I stept up to him, took him by the collar, and asked him what business he had with that plate; he said he had none.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I went to the house with no bad intent. I had the foul disease and went for advice; they surprised me so, that I had no opportunity of telling my intent in going there.</p>
